Aggressive auto-select no longer auto-marks Ref-tier "—" passengers for deletion. A file pulled into a duplicate group by a same-stem pair edge (RAW+JPG, HEIC+JPG, or a Live Photo's video) is shown as a "—" passenger and is now never auto-tagged for delete, so a complementary original can't be silently swept; only files the scanner positively classified as exact or near-duplicates remain eligible (#536).
